# drivers/meraki/Kconfig

menu "Meraki Devices"

config MERAKI_CONFIG
	bool "Meraki Board Data support"
	depends on I2C
	---help---
          This option enables support for the meraki-config device, which
	  proxies the content of the board ID EEPROM to a known location.

	  It also provides kernel access to the Meraki product type.

	  If your board has a board ID EEPROM on it, say Y here.

config CISCO_MPS_SUPPORT
       bool "Cisco Archimedes-family modular power supply support"
       depends on I2C
       default n
       ---help---
         This option enables driver support for interfacing with up to
         two external Archimedes-family Cisco power supplies over I2C
         and GPIOs.

         Say N here if you don't know whether or not your device has
         these power supplies.

config CISCO_RPS_SUPPORT
       bool "Cisco RPS 2300 driver support"
       depends on I2C
       default n
       ---help---
         This option enables support for interfacing with an external
         Cisco RPS 2300 over I2C and GPIOs.

         Say N here if you don't know whether or not your device
         supports the Cisco RPS 2300.

endmenu
